  abstract  = {We investigate the stability of instance-dependent cost-sensitive (IDCS) classifiers and their SHAP/LIME explanations under class imbalance. Our results show that explanations applied to such models are significantly less stable, especially under high class imbalance, with implications for banking regulations on transparency and explainability.},
